page.title: 12Warburg Nature Reserve
page.content: The nature reserve is 250 acres large. The land was given to BBONT(Berks Bucks Oxon Naturalists Trust)in 1968 and it became a nature reserve.It is open all the time but the information centre is open Saturday to Wednesday 9 to 6 o'clock.Visitors come from all over England and they have about 14000 a year.The most common animal is a Bank Vole.There are some stuffed animals such as a badger,a fox,a otter and 5 others.There is a library and there is a warden.There is a rifle range that was in use 15 years ago.There is a pond there.It was made in the last 2 months. There are rare flowers such as a bee orchid,a fly orchid and bird nest orchid.
